{{Quote|Oh, he doesn't have to die, if his Jedi power can neutralize my Sith poison!|[[Satal Keto/Legends|Satal Keto]]|audio=SithPoison-DLOTS.flac|<ref name="DLOTSA">[[Tales of the Jedi: Dark Lords of the Sith (audio drama)|''Tales of the Jedi: Dark Lords of the Sith'' audio drama]]</ref>}}
'''Sith poison''' was a biological toxin, and a product of [[Sith alchemy/Legends|Sith alchemy]], that when absorbed in sufficient quantity, multiplied the rage felt by a person. In action it was more of a disease, taking up residence in the victim's body and setting off chemical reactions that rapidly diminished the victim's ability to resist the pull of the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] of [[The Force/Legends|the Force]]. The poison could be fatal unless counteracted by strong [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] powers, and even then its effects were likely to remain.

==Description==
{{Quote|It is the anger&hellip;the anger ignites the Sith poison&hellip;|Satal Keto|<ref name="Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith 5">[[Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith 5|''Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith'' 5]]</ref>}}
Sith poison could either be ingested or administered by medical means, usually via syringe; both of these methods brought a much shorter reaction time upon the victim. It could even be directly applied through the mucus membranes of an already exposed injury.<ref name="DSS">''[[The Dark Side Sourcebook]]''</ref>

After being introduced to the body, the poison is absorbed on a molecular level, feeding on the individual's anger and drawing them closer to the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]]. The individual's judgment becomes less rational, and they eventually become so enraged that they begin to lash out involuntarily with the dark side.<ref name="DSS" />

Use of Sith poison was extremely rare, therefore being implemented by only the most proficient [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] [[Sith alchemist/Legends|alchemists]]. While creating the infusion the alchemist expends much of their own dark side energy; the process is laborious. Once the toxin is finished the alchemist then has a powerful weapon to use against any unsuspecting [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]].<ref name="DSS" />

==Notable use==
[[Krath/Legends|Krath]] leader [[Satal Keto/Legends|Satal Keto]] injected [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Ulic Qel-Droma/Legends|Ulic Qel-Droma]] with a syringe full of Sith poison shortly before the [[Great Sith War/Legends|Great Sith War]], when Ulic came to [[Cinnagar/Legends|Cinnagar]] posing as a [[Dark Jedi/Legends|fallen Jedi]]. Qel-Droma suffered the full effects of the poison instantly, and involuntarily released the dark side with such [[Telekinesis/Legends#Force Wave|force]] that he destroyed the Krath [[Torture/Legends|torture]] device he was harnessed to.<ref name="DLOTS4">[[Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith 4|''Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith'' 4]]</ref><ref name="DLOTSA" /> Qel-Droma suffered from outbursts from then on, up until it drove him into [[Battle of Ossus (Great Sith War)|murdering his own brother]], [[Cay Qel-Droma]]. The sudden shock of Cay's death broke the dark side's thrall over Ulic, and of the poison's torment as well.<ref name="TSW">[[Tales of the Jedi – The Sith War 5|''Tales of the Jedi – The Sith War'' 5]]</ref>

During the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], the Dark Jedi [[Thaum Rystra]] used [[Sith sorcery/Legends|Sith sorcery]] to fix stingers to the [[Lekku/Legends|lekku]] of the [[Twi'lek/Legends|Twi'lek]] [[Desvin Tor'thal]], that could fire Sith poison.<ref name="LoD">"[[Light and Dark (adventure)|Light and Dark]]"</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
Sith poison was first introduced in the [[Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith|''Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi - Dark Lords of the Sith'']] story arc, and was one plot device among many used to develop the story of Ulic Qel-Droma's progression down the dark side.<ref name="DLOTS4" /><ref name="DLOTSA" /> It was later elaborated on in the ''[[The Dark Side Sourcebook]]'', a supplemental guide for the ''[[Star Wars Roleplaying Game]]''.<ref name="DSS" />

